# Agent Collaboration And Role Separation

The agent identity that authored a unit of work does not act as the primary auditor for that same unit.

## Source Of Truth

- `docs/planning/AGENT-WORKFLOW.md`
- `docs/planning/AUDIT-PROTOCOL.md`

## What To Record

- author identity
- intended auditor identity
- tier
- degraded-mode status

## What To Avoid

- treating same-identity subagents as cross-identity review
- silently flipping roles
- silently editing a handoff output instead of opening a new audit round
- claiming closure while companion review is still missing on high-risk work
